1
00:00:06,050 --> 00:00:08,030
Jellal Fernandez...

2
00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:14,030
I hereby place you under arrest for the 
crime of high treason against the state.

3
00:01:51,960 --> 00:01:53,420
Please, wait!

4
00:01:59,790 --> 00:02:02,410
A Guild for Only One.

5
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:09,420
Jellal has lost his memories!

6
00:02:09,420 --> 00:02:11,610
He doesn't remember a thing!

7
00:02:11,860 --> 00:02:16,330
By clause 13 of the criminal code, 
that is not a valid defense.

8
00:02:20,050 --> 00:02:22,100
You can release them from the runes now.

9
00:02:23,460 --> 00:02:24,410
But...!

10
00:02:24,410 --> 00:02:27,740
It's okay. I have no intention of resisting.

11
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:36,130
I never was able to remember you...

12
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:44,140
I am truly sorry, Wendy...

13
00:02:44,970 --> 00:02:48,900
She tells me that long 
ago, she was saved by you.

14
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:53,560
I see.

15
00:02:55,060 --> 00:02:58,720
I do not know how much suffering 
I must have caused all of you.

16
00:02:59,380 --> 00:03:03,280
But to hear that I saved 
someone makes me glad.

17
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:08,980
Erza.

18
00:03:16,140 --> 00:03:18,020
Thank you for everything.

19
00:03:24,430 --> 00:03:25,730
I must stop him.

20
00:03:35,700 --> 00:03:37,740
It's for me to stop him.

21
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:41,080
Jellal is going away...

22
00:03:43,730 --> 00:03:48,160
Jellal, finally awakened from 
his long nightmare, is...

23
00:03:49,970 --> 00:03:54,680
How can I just let him be shut 
up in the darkness yet again?

24
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:57,470
Is there nothing left you wish to say?

25
00:04:05,450 --> 00:04:09,060
It's pretty much guaranteed you'll be 
executed or given life without parole.

26
00:04:09,710 --> 00:04:11,120
But that's...

27
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:14,830
You'll never see another human face again.

28
00:04:17,690 --> 00:04:18,580
No...

29
00:04:21,900 --> 00:04:23,490
I won't let you take him!

30
00:04:23,490 --> 00:04:25,820
You ain't takin' him!

31
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:28,440
Natsu!

32
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:29,870
They're from the Council!

33
00:04:31,880 --> 00:04:32,410
Why, you...

34
00:04:32,410 --> 00:04:33,630
Move it!

35
00:04:35,190 --> 00:04:37,880
He's our ally!

36
00:04:38,630 --> 00:04:40,840
We're takin' him back with us!

37
00:04:43,090 --> 00:04:44,440
Natsu-san...

38
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:47,550
L-Leave me be...

39
00:04:47,550 --> 00:04:49,200
Restrain them!

40
00:04:57,060 --> 00:04:58,790
Go, Natsu!

41
00:04:58,790 --> 00:04:59,990
Gray?

42
00:05:00,730 --> 00:05:04,690
There's no stopping Natsu now, after all!

43
00:05:06,260 --> 00:05:08,490
It don't sit right!

44
00:05:08,490 --> 00:05:10,780
He helped defend you from Nirvana!

45
00:05:10,780 --> 00:05:14,370
And you don't got even one word of thanks?!

46
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:17,710
There is truth to that.

47
00:05:17,710 --> 00:05:20,500
It is unjust to arrest a man like that!

48
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:25,720
It pains me to say it, but if that man 
is taken away, Erza-san will be saddened!

49
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:30,440
Don't blame me if anyone gets hurt!

50
00:05:31,310 --> 00:05:34,930
Please! Don't take Jellal with you!

51
00:05:36,300 --> 00:05:37,940
Come here, Jellal!

52
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:41,800
You can't leave Erza!

53
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:44,990
You've got to stay by her side! For her!

54
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:50,620
So come here! We stand with you!

55
00:05:50,860 --> 00:05:52,430
We're allies, right?!

56
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:55,450
Arrest them all!

57
00:05:55,450 --> 00:05:58,420
For obstructing government officials 
and aiding in the escape of a criminal!

58
00:06:10,340 --> 00:06:11,570
Enough!

59
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:13,810
That's far enough!

60
00:06:17,590 --> 00:06:19,410
I apologize for the fuss we've caused.

61
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:23,770
I... will take full responsibility.

62
00:06:27,050 --> 00:06:28,280
Jellal...

63
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,230
Take him.

64
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:40,330
Erza!

65
00:06:40,330 --> 00:06:41,200
Sit down!

66
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:41,850
Yes, ma'am.

67
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,130
Oh, right...

68
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:00,390
It was the color of your hair.

69
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:15,030
Farewell, Erza.

70
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:57,940
Where did Erza go?

71
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:03,430
Let's leave her alone for a little while.

72
00:08:03,750 --> 00:08:04,620
Aye...

73
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:12,520
To hear that I saved someone makes me glad.

74
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:29,550
Jellal Fernandez.

75
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:31,730
Whoa, that's hard to remember!

76
00:08:32,550 --> 00:08:34,810
That name's gonna tie my tongue in knots!

77
00:08:35,280 --> 00:08:39,980
Your name, "Wally Buchanan", 
seems hard to remember, too.

78
00:08:40,470 --> 00:08:42,580
Erza, how about you?

79
00:08:42,850 --> 00:08:44,680
I am Erza.

80
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:47,540
Just plain Erza.

81
00:08:48,110 --> 00:08:50,040
That's kind of sad...

82
00:08:53,980 --> 00:08:55,450
What?

83
00:08:56,150 --> 00:08:57,830
It's a pretty scarlet.

84
00:08:58,650 --> 00:09:00,000
Scarlet?

85
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:03,780
I know! Let's name you "Erza Scarlet"!

86
00:09:03,780 --> 00:09:08,010
"Name you"? Don't just 
go naming other people...

87
00:09:08,010 --> 00:09:09,800
Scarlet...

88
00:09:11,540 --> 00:09:14,690
Erza Scarlet...

89
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:27,110
Scarlet. The color of your hair.

90
00:09:27,450 --> 00:09:29,490
That way, I'll never forget.

91
00:09:33,430 --> 00:09:34,630
Jellal...

92
00:09:42,090 --> 00:09:44,660
That morning's dawn

93
00:09:44,660 --> 00:09:47,290
was painted a beautiful scarlet,

94
00:09:47,290 --> 00:09:49,740
the likes of which I had never seen before.

95
00:09:51,970 --> 00:09:54,920
Like the color of Erza's hair,

96
00:09:54,920 --> 00:09:57,980
it was warm, and passionate...

97
00:10:02,690 --> 00:10:07,430
If she could only lift her face, a beautiful 
sky would be spread out before her...

98
00:10:10,010 --> 00:10:11,890
If she could only lift her face...

99
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:39,210
So cute!

100
00:10:39,820 --> 00:10:43,990
Oh? I'm far cuter.

101
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:47,930
The entire village here is part of the guild,

102
00:10:47,930 --> 00:10:50,500
so clothing production 
is a thriving business!

103
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:54,050
Is it some kind of Nirvit traditional sewing?

104
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:58,390
Now that I think about it... Maybe it is?

105
00:10:58,390 --> 00:11:04,260
You didn't realize that the guild was 
all descendants of the Nirvit, did you?

106
00:11:04,260 --> 00:11:06,960
Well, I'm the only one who joined afterwards.

107
00:11:08,310 --> 00:11:11,710
Erza, won't you try them 
on? They're really cute!

108
00:11:13,260 --> 00:11:15,480
Sure... You're right.

109
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:24,280
Speaking of which, Wendy... When did 
Caitshelter join the League of Guilds?

110
00:11:24,280 --> 00:11:29,500
I apologize for being blunt, 
but until this mission began,

111
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:32,950
I had not even heard your guild's name.

112
00:11:32,950 --> 00:11:34,960
Now that you mention it, neither had I.

113
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:36,840
Is that so?

114
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:41,340
My guild must really be one 
of the more obscure ones...

115
00:11:41,340 --> 00:11:45,090
Who cares? Everyone is waiting...

116
00:11:47,730 --> 00:11:49,490
Fairy Tail...

117
00:11:49,970 --> 00:11:51,780
Blue Pegasus...

118
00:11:52,070 --> 00:11:53,730
Lamia Scale...

119
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:56,270
Also, Wendy and Carla.

120
00:11:57,590 --> 00:12:03,570
You have done well in defeating 
Oracion Seis and stopping Nirvana.

121
00:12:03,980 --> 00:12:07,320
As a representative for the 
local League of Guilds,

122
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:09,990
I, Robaul, say job well done.

123
00:12:10,450 --> 00:12:12,040
Thank you.

124
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:13,910
Nabula!

125
00:12:13,910 --> 00:12:15,640
Thank you!

126
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:19,520
It was our pleasure, Master Robaul!

127
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:24,470
The fight with Oracion Seis was 
one fierce battle after the next!

128
00:12:24,710 --> 00:12:29,210
There was not a single easy battle!

129
00:12:29,560 --> 00:12:32,180
But the bonds between us allies

130
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:36,220
led us on the path to victory!

131
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:38,540
You said it, Sensei!

132
00:12:38,540 --> 00:12:39,590
Men.

133
00:12:39,590 --> 00:12:42,660
Oh sure, just take all the 
good parts for yourself.

134
00:12:42,660 --> 00:12:43,370
Men.

135
00:12:43,670 --> 00:12:46,780
Did he even fight anyone?

136
00:12:46,780 --> 00:12:48,790
It's finally over...

137
00:12:48,790 --> 00:12:51,430
You two did well yourself!

138
00:12:51,430 --> 00:12:52,790
Jura-san...

139
00:12:52,790 --> 00:12:55,290
You're supposed to throw a party now, right?

140
00:12:55,290 --> 00:12:56,500
Aye, sir!

141
00:12:58,350 --> 00:12:59,470
Ichiya...

142
00:12:59,470 --> 00:12:59,960
Ichiya...

143
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:00,920
...will join in!

144
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:02,340
...will join in!

145
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:07,750
A party?

146
00:13:07,750 --> 00:13:09,260
And off go the clothes!

147
00:13:10,170 --> 00:13:11,470
You, too!

148
00:13:19,330 --> 00:13:23,280
Now... Everyone from Caitshelter, join in!

149
00:13:53,650 --> 00:13:55,120
Everyone...

150
00:13:55,680 --> 00:14:01,690
I am truly sorry about hiding 
our legacy as Nirvit.

151
00:14:04,440 --> 00:14:07,380
You ruined the mood to say that?

152
00:14:07,380 --> 00:14:09,800
We really don't mind at all.

153
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:10,900
Right?

154
00:14:10,900 --> 00:14:12,120
Right!

155
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:15,980
Master, I don't mind either.

156
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:24,500
Everyone, please listen carefully 
to what I am about to say.

157
00:14:29,210 --> 00:14:35,350
To start, we are not the 
descendants of the Nirvit.

158
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:41,100
We are the Nirvit themselves!

159
00:14:42,310 --> 00:14:48,570
400 years ago, it was I who created Nirvana.

160
00:14:49,040 --> 00:14:49,990
What?

161
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:51,490
No way!

162
00:14:51,940 --> 00:14:54,030
400 years ago?

163
00:15:01,390 --> 00:15:07,440
400 years ago, in order to stop the 
war that was raging across the world,

164
00:15:08,020 --> 00:15:13,960
I created Nirvana, a magic that 
inverts light and darkness.

165
00:15:15,390 --> 00:15:20,600
Nirvana became our country,

166
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:25,480
and, for a time, we realized peace.

167
00:15:27,010 --> 00:15:28,110
However...

168
00:15:30,390 --> 00:15:36,120
Great power will, without fail, give 
rise to a great power opposing it.

169
00:15:37,640 --> 00:15:44,080
As much as Nirvana changed darkness for 
light, Nirvana itself became wrapped in darkness.

170
00:15:46,300 --> 00:15:48,710
It was to maintain balance.

171
00:15:49,410 --> 00:15:55,620
It was impossible to change people's 
personalities to light without limit.

172
00:15:57,050 --> 00:16:00,300
As light rises to oppose the darkness,

173
00:16:00,300 --> 00:16:04,020
so does darkness rise to oppose 
the light, without fail.

174
00:16:04,610 --> 00:16:07,450
Now that you mention it...

175
00:16:21,650 --> 00:16:28,460
The darkness lost from the various 
peoples came back upon us Nirvit.

176
00:16:29,040 --> 00:16:30,190
No...

177
00:16:33,260 --> 00:16:35,130
It was hell.

178
00:16:41,480 --> 00:16:46,990
We killed each other... 
Until no one was left.

179
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:57,780
I am the only survivor.

180
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:07,090
Well, at this point, 
that's not exactly right.

181
00:17:07,890 --> 00:17:15,630
My physical body has long perished... I am 
what you might call a spectral form now.

182
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:26,120
Or rather, a weak ghost trying to 
atone for his sins of the past.

183
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:36,280
I watched over Nirvana for 400 years until 
someone appeared who would be able to destroy it.

184
00:17:38,950 --> 00:17:40,060
And now...

185
00:17:42,050 --> 00:17:45,410
...my role is finally over.

186
00:17:52,830 --> 00:17:55,090
W-What are you saying...?

187
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:06,030
What is this?

188
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:07,250
Everyone?

189
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:08,480
All of you!

190
00:18:08,480 --> 00:18:10,940
Magna! Pepel!

191
00:18:11,210 --> 00:18:12,760
What's going on here?

192
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:14,560
They're all disappearing!

193
00:18:15,190 --> 00:18:17,730
No! Everyone!

194
00:18:18,030 --> 00:18:20,490
I don't want you to disappear!

195
00:18:22,850 --> 00:18:26,960
I apologize for deceiving you...

196
00:18:27,650 --> 00:18:34,140
All the members of the guild 
are illusions created by me.

197
00:18:36,830 --> 00:18:38,260
Say what?!

198
00:18:38,520 --> 00:18:40,950
Illusions with their own personalities?

199
00:18:41,290 --> 00:18:43,680
What incredible magic power!

200
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:47,700
I...

201
00:18:48,450 --> 00:18:54,580
...lived alone in these 
ruins, protecting Nirvana.

202
00:18:55,690 --> 00:19:00,570
7 years ago, a single boy came here.

203
00:19:06,410 --> 00:19:08,920
Please, take care of this girl!

204
00:19:09,490 --> 00:19:15,670
I couldn't turn down the request of 
that boy and his fierce, honest eyes.

205
00:19:17,350 --> 00:19:21,380
Even though I had promised 
myself I would stay alone...

206
00:19:22,820 --> 00:19:25,680
Mister, where am I?

207
00:19:27,060 --> 00:19:29,180
T-This is...

208
00:19:29,180 --> 00:19:30,510
Jellal?

209
00:19:32,300 --> 00:19:35,370
He said he was taking me to a guild...

210
00:19:35,370 --> 00:19:37,920
T-This is a guild!

211
00:19:37,920 --> 00:19:40,960
This is a Wizard's Guild!

212
00:19:40,960 --> 00:19:42,070
Really?

213
00:19:42,360 --> 00:19:43,960
Nabula!

214
00:19:43,960 --> 00:19:45,930
Try going outside!

215
00:19:46,650 --> 00:19:49,380
You have friends waiting for you.

216
00:19:52,100 --> 00:19:55,820
And so I also created an illusory family.

217
00:19:56,170 --> 00:19:58,840
The guild was created all for Wendy?

218
00:19:59,390 --> 00:20:01,860
I don't wanna hear that!

219
00:20:02,270 --> 00:20:04,800
Bask, Naoki, don't you disappear too!

220
00:20:05,320 --> 00:20:11,680
Wendy, Carla... You no longer 
need a foster family.

221
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:22,530
Don't you have real friends now?

222
00:20:32,620 --> 00:20:38,800
Your future... has only just begun.

223
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:41,130
Master!

224
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:47,130
Everyone, truly, thank you.

225
00:20:48,900 --> 00:20:52,100
I leave Wendy and Carla in your hands.

226
00:21:17,550 --> 00:21:20,880
Master!

227
00:21:56,590 --> 00:22:06,190
Bury the pain of losing your loved 
ones... into the arms of your friends.

228
00:22:17,290 --> 00:22:17,930
Come.

229
00:22:19,550 --> 00:22:20,970
To Fairy Tail.

230
00:23:55,670 --> 00:23:58,850
It feels like it's been a while 
since we've been back to the guild.

231
00:23:58,850 --> 00:23:59,670
No kidding!

232
00:23:59,670 --> 00:24:01,570
We can finally take it easy!

233
00:24:01,570 --> 00:24:03,770
Actually, it doesn't look like we can.

234
00:24:03,770 --> 00:24:06,810
I heard there's a person that saw a dragon!

235
00:24:06,810 --> 00:24:07,500
Seriously?!

236
00:24:07,770 --> 00:24:10,350
Could that dragon be Igneel?

237
00:24:10,350 --> 00:24:14,160
Maybe it's the Dragon that Wendy 
and Carla are looking for!

238
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:16,590
Next time: Call of the Dragon.

239
00:24:16,590 --> 00:24:20,940
Oh yeah... What was the name of the 
dragon they were looking for again?

240
00:24:20,940 --> 00:24:23,020
I'm pretty sure it's "Wendine".

241
00:24:23,020 --> 00:24:24,520
Uh, I think you're mixed up.

242
00:24:24,520 --> 00:24:26,870


